The paper deals with natural language interfaces and visual data exploration, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of models of distributional semantics to find and rank entity properties is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses the Wikidata dataset, which is a large-scale knowledge graph, making it relevant to the database (cs.DB) sub-category.
